# do not specify --with-pc-path=
# pkgconfig does the proper thing when ELF64 are in lib64 and ELF32 are in lib

# glib and pkgconfig have recursive requirements upon each other

with version stable 0.28 0.27.1 0.27
#with base    glib
with also    --with-installed-glib --enable-shared=yes --enable-static=no
with role    development
with trait   console makej solo
with source  http://pkgconfig.freedesktop.org/releases/pkg-config-$VERSION.tar.gz
with info    last 20130125
with info    home http://www.freedesktop.org/
with info    freecode pkg-config
with info    cite 'system for managing library compile/link flags.
pkgconfig is a system for managing library compile/link
flags that works with automake and autoconf.
It replaces the ubiquitous *-config scripts.'
